commitResults.messageTitle: Edit FindCommand to match coding standard

commitResults.messageBody: * To make the Ui method names sound clearer, precede Ui method names with "display"

There are no checks done to prevent programmer's mistakes. These include
FXML components being improperly configured and the storage file not
existing.

Add assertions to check for these mistakes and print out an error
message.

Using assertions is preferable over exceptions as assertions indicate
that the programmer has made a mistake in their code rather than a
mistake made by the user.

Although the code worked fine, the code could have been more readable.
There were also some assumptions made about the user's input such as
the user's commands containing spaces. These assumptions can be
dangerous as runtime errors can occur.

Add more classes for commands. Add more exceptions to handle more user
inputs.
